d class=3D"r"><div style=3D"margin-left:-20px"><ul style=3D"margin-top:0;ma=
rgin-bottom:0;list-style-type:revert;"><li style=3D"Margin:0 0 24px 0;"><em=
>The de minimis
exception</em>: The ubiquitous buzzwords <em>sustainability </em>and <em>ca=
psule collection</em> have a new companion in the modern argot of the indus=
try: the <em>de minimis </em>exception, which refers to imports or online o=
rders valued at $800 or less that are able to enter the United States witho=
ut the recipient paying tariffs or going through formal customs procedures =
and protocols. Shein and Temu have built their entire businesses around shi=
pping inexpensive products from
China that are covered by the <em>de minimis </em>exception. It=E2=80=99s o=
bviously another story for luxury retailers, like Ssense. When you order th=
at <a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2U=
ktxclJLZ0dVMDRhRVVZUVNUNU0wSnVRelRTVT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9nby5zaG9wbXku=
dXMvcC0xMjc2MTY5Mz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249TGluZStTaGVldCstK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODI=
lMkY0JTJGMjUlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fY29udGVudD1MaW5lK1NoZWV0Ky0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJT=
I4MiUyRjQlMkYyNSUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWxfYWN0aW9uXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Nvd=
XJjZT1jdXN0b21lci5pb1x1MDAyNnV0bV90ZXJtPWY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImludGVy=
bmFsIjoiZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6MjA2OTEyNX0/b1ac283909f67b1=
3b956d845b225bd398119c6a9aba59a16c2a05138ebb0ac63" style=3D"text-decoration=
:underline;color:#d40000;">Dries Van Noten slip dress</a> for $975, you=E2=
=80=99re going over the $800 threshold, so additional import taxes apply.<b=
r/><br/>Now, amid <strong>Trump</strong>=E2=80=99s new tariff era, the <em>=
de minimis </em>exception is toast. For Mexico and Canada, tariffs have bee=
n paused
for 30 days, but 10 percent levies are scheduled to go into effect for Chin=
a today, and they include a provision that closes the <em>de minimis </em>l=
oophole. All these goods will incur a tax on top of the purchase, likely ca=
using retailers to meaningfully adjust their sales forecasts, prices, and m=
ore.=C2=A0</li><li style=3D"Margin:0 0 24px 0;"><em>Resizing the cost stack=
</em>: Meanwhile, retailers, analysts, and consumers are trying to decipher=
 how the tariffs will impact prices and be
passed on to buyers. Indeed, tariffs are just another cost input, albeit on=
e wrapped in political drama, and retailers can manage them in three main w=
ays. They can always just raise prices, which is the inflationary option. O=
r they could <em>technically</em> accept the reduced margins and try to off=
set them with increased volume=E2=80=94a practical challenge for any fiscal=
ly responsible company operating at scale. The third option would require c=
utting costs elsewhere in the operating stack (supply
chain, manufacturing, packaging, etcetera).<br/><br/>The likely result of t=
hese tariffs is that strong brands, which offer beloved or essential produc=
ts, will more easily be able to pass some of the new cost on to the custome=
r. Others will be maneuvering through a game of margins, carefully reducing=
 costs in nonessential areas=E2=80=94say, paring back a splashy new marketi=
ng campaign or postponing a store renovation. But <em>everyone</em> is hopi=
ng that these new taxes are temporary, perhaps a negotiating
lever with trade partners, and not the new status quo. (It=E2=80=99s also n=
ot entirely clear that this is, strictly speaking, <a href=3D"https://email=
=2Epuck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVD=
J4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dVMDRhRVVZUVNUNU0w=
SnVRelRTVT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucG9saXRpY28uY29tL25ld3MvMjAyNS8wMi8=
wMy90cnVtcC10YXJpZmZzLWxlZ2FsLTAwMjAyMDYzP3V0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1MaW5lK1NoZWV0Ky=
0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MiUyRjQlMkYyNSUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9jb250ZW50PUxpbmUrU2hlZ=
XQrLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgyJTJGNCUyRjI1JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbF9h=
Y3Rpb25cdTAwMjZ1dG1fc291cmNlPWN1c3RvbWVyLmlvXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Rlcm09ZjZjNjA2MTd=
kYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwiaW50ZXJuYWwiOiJmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJsaW5rX2lkIjoyMD=
Y5MTI2fQ/b2a694c661c4715e0ae609a142005cc08512ad9e8c098d29de2afd4ca217dca0" =
style=3D"text-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;">legal</a>.)</li><li styl=
e=3D"Margin:0 0 24px 0;"><em>Survivor: Retail Edition=E2=80=A6</em>: Execut=
ives at the highest level of the fashion industry are always factoring exog=
enous risks, like recessions and natural disasters, into their business mod=
els
and long-term planning. And these tariffs, while shocking, shouldn=E2=80=99=
t have caught any C-suite <em>totally </em>off-guard, given that Trump talk=
ed about tariffs constantly during the campaign. There are a number of best=
-practice protocols for black swan economic environments, like this one, an=
d I expect you=E2=80=99ll see some of these initiatives rolled out across t=
he retail industry, depending on how long this trade war lasts.<br/><br/>Fi=
rst, retailers will consider diversifying their supplier base. Over
the years, we=E2=80=99ve seen companies de-lever their relationship with, s=
ay, China or Mexico by finding partners in South East Asia and South Americ=
a. I expect this to continue, although it=E2=80=99s a time-consuming and la=
borious process. One strategist I spoke with recalled the era when =E2=80=
=9Ctube tops=E2=80=9D were taxed differently than =E2=80=9Cshirts,=E2=80=9D=
 an economic wrinkle that led to a profusion of the garment entering the co=
untry. In the A.I. era, retailers can more easily leverage data analytics t=
o identify sweet spots in
pricing where even a significant increase won=E2=80=99t significantly impac=
t sales volume, ultimately boosting profits despite potential tariff pressu=
res.<br/><br/>Also, I expect retailers will become more communicative about=
 tax implications with their customers, perhaps by adding more FAQs or deta=
ils to the shipping and returns section. Rather than allow customers to won=
der if they=E2=80=99re going to be impacted by customs or taxes when orderi=
ng from overseas, brands and companies should be forthcoming about
the downstream economics. In the end, it will remove a hurdle before purcha=
se. Who knows, maybe the <em>de minimis </em>exception will end up on a cam=
paign poster one day. (Let=E2=80=99s hope not=E2=80=A6)</li></ul></div>
